er <b>1 min\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add eggs, milk and vanilla, then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt, then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix for a further <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Remove hot fruit from oven and carefully spread sponge mixture evenly over fruit. Sprinkle with extra sugar and bake for 45-50 minutes (170°C), until a wooden skewer inserted into the centre of sponge comes out clean. Serve warm (see Tips)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can use apples of choice and milk of choice in this recipe.","If using frozen feijoas, defrost completely and drain off any excess moisture before using.","You can find stem ginger at gourmet food stores or online. If stem ginger isn't available, you can replace it with minced crystallised ginger.","Serve with cream, custard or ice cream if desired.","<strong>Gluten free feijoa sponge pudding:<\/strong> Replace plain flour and baking powder with gluten free versions"],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 20m","6 portions"]}